What occurs within the eye when a person first reads a book and then looks up to see a far off mountain in the distance: W) Ciliary muscles go first relax, and then contract X) The Suspensory ligaments first relax and then contract Y) The Lens first become flat, and then becomes rounder Z) Choroid is first pulled away from the lens, and then it is pulled towards it

choices.W: Ciliary muscles go first relax, and then contract
choices.X: The Suspensory ligaments first relax and then contract
choices.Y: The Lens first become flat, and then becomes rounder
choices.Z: Choroid is first pulled away from the lens, and then it is pulled towards it

answer: X) THE SUSPENSORY LIGAMENTS FIRST RELAX AND THEN CONTRACT
